Module:

Modules are simply files with the “. py” extension containing Python code that can be imported inside another Python Program.

Modules-> Collections of functions, classes(variable + method)

Functions:
1)How to create a module
2)How to call the function from one module to another module
3)Same function in 2 modules

Class(Variable&Method)
1)Same method in different module

Approach:
import module_name
from module_name import class/method name/*

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Packages:

Collection of modules is a Package.
Package is a high level entity.

Structure:
  Package--->module1--->function
         --->module2--->function

whenever python package is created, it will create a python file automatically.
